		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I got a powerpak instead fits my entire library of games plus some and
<br />runs on original nes hardware cpu. i guess for a project would be nice to try but as a emulator machine kind of expensive. You can get a better result with a $40.00 nintendo + $135.00 powerpak as far as having games
<br />at your finger tips.  To answer your question i made one 3 years ago ran Mame on it and was pretty cool but when you add cpu motherboard memory controller case ( old nes) + controller and operating system it can get very expensive quick, Not including a good power supply. also cooling was a issue for me, it got really hot.

		

		</td>
